<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">a_cleric</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Please include server and price range.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hunon Hillmover</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Server: Rodcet Nife<BR>What happened is I made tow different trades for two different bracers, and each trade was the same: a RMB + DM gaunts<P>RMB = 800pp (avg)<BR>DM gaunts = 600pp (avg)<P>So total is around 1400pp.  More than fair to me!  Especially with the cleric AC bonus.  My theory is that you should really only buy from other clerics, because then the weatlh is shared around.<P><P>------------------<BR>Hunon Hillmover<BR>Dwarven Cleric of Brell<BR>Rodcet Nife</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Folan Vitalis</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I would not pay more then 300 plat for them. <BR>Why? because this more then covers the cost of the 2 plat bars and if you start paying 1400 for them every one that see regis will just kill him for the cash and no cleric will be able to complete their own quest.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tiganos</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Same, I wouldn't pay more than 300pp either, and it's easier to go out and get them yourself.<P>I've gotten 6 so far. 2 for myself. 2 for a guildmate, and traded one of mine for 2 RMB's once, since my druid wife needed them very badly and a level 50 cleric wanted one of them, so I accepted the trade, gave her the bracers, camped him again.<P>Here's where it got fun: AFTER 2 days, I managed to replace mine. I got a tell from that same 50 cleric (who was waiting around in NK for a res on a planes raid).. He had found Zahal. No clerics were camping Regis. He wanted us to come and help him take Regis out for the SAME guildmate I got the two bracers for (Guildmate was present both times, and was about level 28 or so), and the level 50 didn't realize that Grumbel had two already. He also didn't have two bracers himself yet, and no one else was camping Regis, so we killed Regis for the level 50, and he got his second bracer too. Some kindnesses make me very happy in the long run, especially the cooperative kinds. He tried to do something nice for us, and for my guildmate, I felt it was the least we could do.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wynona Brownbeaver</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I gave up on this quest. The bracer is the only piece of quest armor I lack, other than the crappy shield. I spent a few days camping NK and had too many run-ins from druids to make it worth my time. <P>On Mith marr the bracer sells for 1.5-2k, same price range as RMB. I will pay no more than 600pp which is a very fair price considering the rarity of the item versus it being class specific and questable instead of dropped. Too bad all the lvl 50s on my server who don't care about PP anymore throw 2k at a druid like it was nothing, justifying the whole mess.<P>------------------<BR><B>Wynona Jugg</B> - lvl 40 Dwarven cleric<BR><I>Mith Marr</I></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Morrun</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I must have gotten really lucky a couple of days ago.  Well, fairly lucky...<P>I zoned into N Karana, on my way to Rathe Mountains.  Cast my customary Sense Dead upon zoning in from East Karana.  Regis the Reverent.  Woot!<P>/shout anyone camping Zahal?<P>silence<P>Right!  Charge off there and kill him, I think to myself, should be easy enough.  It's only after I've engaged him, I realise I entered the fight with 60% mana...  (if that last holy might hadn't been resisted, I would have lived.  As it was, I had a mad dash back from Rivervale, praying that no one else would find him)<P>So, 10 minutes or so later I'm back in North Karana, and he's still up!  This time, I don't let excitement rule my judgement, and I wait for a warrior friend.  No trouble this time, he went down quickly.<P>After that we proceeded to drop Grimrot, getting me a scythe... so I wasn't too worried about one death  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>As for prices on the bracer, 300pp is the max I'd consider paying.  I might trade one for an RMB (now that I have two bracers, heh), but to be honest, I'd rather have the AC for now.<P>As someone else pointed out, paying 1400pp for one is bad news, it just encourages other classes to farm it (and I know that happens, there are two people on my never-help list because of it).<BR><P>------------------<BR>Morrun Catspaw<BR>Halfling Cleric (41st)<BR>Albion - Death Before Dishonour!<BR>Cazic-Thule Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">SolidSnke</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">How about the greeves? Whats a fair price on those..<P>------------------<BR>SolidSnke<BR>                <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Find a lot of bad guys! Because the bad guys want to give you all their loot - otherwise why would they keep coming back ;) Just remember to stand BEHIND the warrior!<BR><HR></BLOCKQUOTE></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tiganos</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I would think no more than 200pp for the greaves. All they need is 1 plat bar (approx 130pp).. The rest, I would consider for their time.<P>It's really easy to get the greaves, btw.<BR></FONT><